Supreme Court, Appellate Term, April, 1898.

Before Beekman, P. J., Gildersleeve and Giegerich, JJ.

Bridget M. Kelly, Appellant, v. John Henry Theiss, Respondent — Appeal from judgment of the General Term of the City Court affirming a judgment in favor of defendant dismissing the complaint of plaintiff. Arthur J. Westermayr, for Appellant; Fromme Bros., for Respondent.

Judgment affirmed, with costs; no opinion.
